NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now as to the bidding. I don't mind Ann bidding 4H. However, she was very inconsistent. 3C asked Stan to bid 4H with either a maximum 2H bid or with some club cards. Stan correctly judged to bid 3H. But Ann bid 4H anyway. So there was no point in bidding 3C if she was going to bid 4H no matter what. |
PG| ***** 105 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|You could make a case in match points, Ann should invite with 3C bid whereas in IMPs I think 4H is quite reasonable over 2H. In IMPs you should bid close games, even ones that are not quite 50% because the game bonus is worth lots of IMPs. But in Match Points, you should only bid games that are favorites to make because the size of the game bonus makes no difference.|
PG| ***** 106 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let's count Ann's declarer points. 12 HCP, 2 length points, 1 quality suit = 15. Once Stan raises she adds 4 for the void and 1 for the 4+-card side club suit which gets her to 20, just enough to bid 4. So I might even bid 4 in match points, but certainly in IMPs and it turns out 4H will often make.|
PG| ***** 107 ***** |


